50|$|New Zealand {{ratified}} the Convention on the Elimination of All Forms of Discrimination Against Women (CEDAW) in 1985. Article 11 provides that states must take appropriate measures to eliminate employment discrimination, including ensuring {{the right to}} <b>equal</b> <b>remuneration,</b> and equal treatment for work of equal value.|$|E
